    "explanation": "<p>Equation of given line when velocity is plotted against position with intercept $$=v_0$$ and slope $$=v_0 / x_0$$ is,</p>\n<p>$$v=-\\frac{v_0 x}{x_0}+v_0$$ ...... (i)</p>\n<p>($$-$$Ve sign is became the slope is decreasing) On differentiating with respect to $$t$$</p>\n<p>$$\\frac{d v}{d t}=-\\frac{v_0}{x_0} \\frac{d x}{d t}+0$$</p>\n<p>or $$\\quad a=-\\frac{v_0}{x_0} v$$ ...... (ii)(</p>\n<p>Putting $$v$$ from Eq. (i) in Eq. (ii),</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\na & =-\\frac{v_0}{x_0}\\left[-\\frac{v_0}{x_0} x+v_0\\right] \\\\\n& =\\frac{v_0^2}{x_0^2} x-\\frac{v_0^2}{x_0}\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>\n<p>Which represents a straight line with positive slope and negative intercept.</p>",
